1 five -year terms, as designated by the Governor. Thereafter, the
2 terms of all members shall be five (5) years.
3 D. A vacancy on the Board shall be filled in the same manner as
4 the original appointment for the balance of the unexpired term.
5 Members may succeed themselves but shall serve no more than two
6 consecutive terms. Each member shall serve until a successor is
7 appointed and qualified.
8 E. Members of the Board may be removed from office for one or
9 more of the following reasons:
10 1. The refusal or inability for any reason to perform the
11 duties of a Board member in an efficient, responsible and
12 professional manner;
13 2. The misuse of office for pecuniary or material gain or for
14 personal advantage for self or another;
15 3. A violation of the laws or rules governing the practice of
16 alcohol and drug counseling; or
17 4. Conviction of a felony as verified by a certified copy of
18 the record of the court of conviction.
19 F. Members of the Board shall serve without compensation, but
20 shall be reimbursed for actual and necessary travel expenses as
21 provided in the State Travel Reimbursement Act.
